Space DMV Core Platform (SDCP‑1.0)

A civilian‑first coordination layer for ground, air, and orbital mobility

---

🌌 Overview

Space DMV Core is a prototype mobility framework designed to unify operator identity, vessel verification, and safety protocols across ground, air, and space domains.

It does not replace state DMVs or federal aviation authorities.
Instead, it provides a neutral, emotionally safe, interoperability layer for future hybrid vehicles and orbital mobility.

This repository contains:

• The core architecture
• The Digital Vessel Verification (DVV) model
• The Safety Protocol Chain (SPC‑1.0)
• The Unified Login Portal (ULP‑1.0)
• The Space DMV v1.0 specification
• A prototype UI (local‑only, no backend)


---

🚀 Mission

To create a civilian‑centered, non‑violent, operator‑respecting mobility platform that prepares society for hybrid ground‑air‑space vehicles without imposing regulation or replacing existing agencies.

Space DMV is:

• Local-first
• Privacy-preserving
• Non-regulatory
• Emotionally safe
• Kid-friendly
• Future-ready


