🛰️ Core Components

1. Unified Login Portal (ULP‑1.0)

A federated identity shell that allows operators to authenticate using:

• DMV‑O (state DMV identity provider)
• FAAO (FAA identity provider)
• Space‑O (Space DMV identity provider)


The portal stores no personal data.
It assembles an Identity Envelope (IE‑1.0) for the session.

---

2. Identity Envelope (IE‑1.0)

A temporary, local-only container that includes:

• Legal name (from DMV‑O)
• State ID token
• Pilot certificate token (optional)
• Space operator token
• Gravity comfort range
• Access needs
• Non‑violent navigation pledge
• Mission context


Used to determine training flows and safety protocols.

---

3. Digital Vessel Verification (DVV)

A DVV is the space-era equivalent of a VIN — extended for hybrid and orbital craft.

DVV includes:

• Vessel name
• Vessel class (ground/air/space hybrid, shuttle, sim-only)
• Owner/operator
• Capabilities
• Safety rating
• Maintenance summary
• Mission history
• Emergency profile


DMV and FAA can verify DVVs via read-only APIs.

---

4. Safety Protocol Chain (SPC‑1.0)

A rules engine that activates based on:

• Operator identity
• Vessel class
• Mission type
• Gravity comfort
• Access needs


Protocols include:

• Non‑violent navigation
• Emergency calm procedures
• Gravity matching
• Hybrid transition safety
• Kid-safe remote participation
• Abort & return logic


This is designed to reduce cognitive load and increase emotional safety.

---

5. Training & Simulation Layer

Scenario-based modules for:

• Hybrid vehicle transitions
• Orbital maneuver basics
• Emergency calm drills
• Family shuttle operations
• Research vessel protocols


All modules are non-violent and operator-respecting.

